INSERT INTO `jos_community_msg` VALUES (1,45,1,0,'Heather Lipford','2011-06-01 17:44:58','Testing','Testing out the message feature'),(2,45,2,0,'Heather Lipford','2011-06-01 17:51:40','Testing messaging','Message message.'),(3,54,2,0,'Joe Sophomore','2011-06-01 17:52:37','RE:Testing messaging','Writing a reply. Blah blah blah.'),(4,42,1,1,'Administrator','2011-06-06 15:24:28','RE:Testing','Looks like it works!'),(5,42,5,0,'Administrator','2011-06-08 12:02:23','yay','did this work'),(6,42,6,0,'Administrator','2011-08-05 02:46:53','Group bug','Hi Adam, \r\nThere was a bug on the site when you registered which automatically made you a member of every school\'s group. I\'ve removed you from all those groups, and I hope you didn\'t get 31 messages telling you that. Thanks for inadvertently helping me find the bug. --Heather (a.k.a. the Admin)'),(7,74,7,0,'Ebe Randeree','2011-08-05 04:23:31','hello','looking forward to catching up in Raleigh '),(8,80,6,0,'adam bronski','2011-08-05 12:25:10','RE:Group bug','Thanks Heather. I was wondering how I got to be a member of all those groups.\n\nAdam'),(9,104,9,0,'Audrey Rorrer','2011-08-07 20:15:14','interview','Ebe, \r\nWhen would your ideal interview time be? \r\nAudrey'),(10,74,10,0,'Ebe Randeree','2011-08-07 23:43:56','Hello','Can you make me the stars admin for the FSU group'),(11,42,10,0,'Administrator','2011-08-08 00:02:14','RE:Hello','Done!  --Heather'),(12,106,12,0,'Brook  Osborne','2011-08-09 20:44:57','feature suggestions','Hi, Heather!  \r\n \r\nI have a couple of quick suggestions for feature improvements. First, when browsing the events pages, it does seem possible to RSVP to an event without clicking through into a specific event. It would be useful to be able to RSVP from the &quot;view all events&quot; page.  \r\n \r\nPoint two: it seems the search feature is case sensitive... this doesn\'t seem optimal.  \r\n \r\nThanks for you presentation, and all of the great work you\'ve done with the site!  \r\n \r\n \r\n-Brook '),(13,45,12,0,'Heather Lipford','2011-08-10 12:55:15','RE:feature suggestions','Thanks for the feedback, great idea about the RSVP and I didn\'t realize that about the search feature.\nThank!\nHeather\n'),(14,111,14,0,'Arpan Chakraborty','2011-08-10 13:04:22','STARS Final Presentation Slide','Hey Brook, \r\n \r\nThis is Arpan from NC State - we spoke yesterday when you came to see my poster on refugee outreach. I prepared NC State\'s slide for the final presentation, and I\'ve mentioned our future collaboration there. I noticed that the slide for Duke University is not there in the STARS Online Resources folder (under Celebration 2011 > Home Team Slides), and was wondering if you were unaware of it. \r\n \r\nYou can take a look at the slides posted there to get an idea of what is expected. Please let me know if you need any assistance. \r\n \r\nMy email address is: achakra@ncsu.edu \r\n \r\nThanks, \r\nArpan'),(15,106,14,0,'Brook  Osborne','2011-08-10 13:21:15','RE:STARS Final Presentation Slide','Hi, Arpan- \n\nThanks for the heads up! I\'ve just posted my slide. See you soon! \n\n\n-Brook '),(16,111,16,0,'Arpan Chakraborty','2011-08-10 13:52:17','NCSU Final Presentation slide updated','Hi Heather, \r\n \r\nI am Arpan, from NC State. I think the online community is turning out to be a great resource. We updated our slide about half an hour ago. I wasn\'t sure if you\'ve already taken a snapshot of the posted files to make the final presentation, so I just wanted to inform you. \r\n \r\nThanks! \r\nArpan'),(17,45,16,0,'Heather Lipford','2011-08-10 13:58:07','RE:NCSU Final Presentation slide updated','Thanks! I\'ll download it again and update the slideshow.\n--Heather\n'),(18,74,18,0,'Ebe Randeree','2011-08-12 20:15:59','check out this video','http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YpP_FM3k478'),(19,119,19,0,'Sandy Keeter','2011-08-14 03:45:15','Accept','Accept'),(20,148,20,0,'Ariana Casale','2011-08-22 20:53:30','email','Hey what\'s your email? Also do you have facebook?'),(21,188,21,0,'Lohit Patil','2011-08-23 18:22:38','will be late for the meeting','will be late for the meeting... i can make it by 5:30pm...'),(22,111,21,0,'Arpan Chakraborty','2011-08-24 05:25:32','RE:will be late for the meeting','Glad to see you on STARS Online. And thanks for trying to accommodate the meeting - I noticed that you had indicated you won\'t be available during this slot, so I was probably going to schedule a meeting with you separately later. But it\'s best if you can come to the common meeting itself. So feel free to come at 5:30 (or as early as possible).'),(23,152,23,0,'Lydia Fritz','2011-08-26 16:48:11','SLC Videos','Can you tell me where to view the SLC videos?  We are a new school and would like to see what others have done.   \r\n \r\nThanks - \r\n \r\nLydia Fritz \r\nUNCG'),(24,211,24,0,'Vivian Williams','2011-08-31 20:33:15','Number','send me your number'),(25,102,24,0,'Bonita O\'Banion','2011-09-02 13:01:02','RE:Number','773-209-9140'),(26,42,23,0,'Administrator','2011-09-02 17:11:03','RE:SLC Videos','Hi Lydia,\n\nWe don\'t have the SLC videos linked anywhere central yet, but we\'ll be working on that. Florida State has a great set of videos available off of their webpages. Check out their website: http://starsalliance.fsu.edu/?page_id=84\n\nHeather\n'),(27,74,19,0,'Ebe Randeree','2011-09-03 19:52:09','RE:Accept','Hi Sandy\n\nHow has the semester been so far?\n'),(28,119,19,0,'Sandy Keeter','2011-09-05 21:25:42','RE:Accept','good!'),(29,273,29,0,'Veronica Catete','2011-09-09 22:16:33','.','.'),(30,166,29,0,'Alok Baikadi','2011-09-09 22:21:26','RE:.','. to you too'),(31,273,29,0,'Veronica Catete','2011-09-09 22:22:45','RE:.','lol I was exploring the stars webpage.  I was testing to see if the send message wrote to the wall like the other message button does\n'),(32,166,29,0,'Alok Baikadi','2011-09-09 22:23:51','RE:.','No problem. How are you doing?'),(33,273,29,0,'Veronica Catete','2011-09-09 22:25:07','RE:.','good.  I don\'t think the message alerts are auto updated.  And I can\'t figure out what the calendar on our profile page is for...  STARS @ Charlotte is a class and I had to register here for homework '),(34,273,29,0,'Veronica Catete','2011-09-09 22:25:14','RE:.','u?'),(35,273,35,0,'Veronica Catete','2011-09-09 22:29:35','Community Resources','Is there any way we can view the digital copies of the celebration posters?  Some posters had interesting stuff that not everyone had the chance to view.  Specifically, I\'m interested in the outreach posters...'),(36,166,29,0,'Alok Baikadi','2011-09-09 22:33:41','RE:.','I\'m hanging in there, being busy. Finally making some progress on my degree.'),(37,273,29,0,'Veronica Catete','2011-09-09 22:40:11','RE:.','That\'s good.  You\'re almost done right?  \n\noh hey, I have to go my roommates are finally ready to leave the lab.  being on campus from 10am until 7 on a Friday is not fun >'),(38,166,29,0,'Alok Baikadi','2011-09-09 22:42:19','RE:.','Yeah, have a great day!'),(39,77,39,0,'Scott Heggen','2011-09-10 13:25:02','Listserv error','Hi Jason, \r\n \r\nI\'m getting the following error for your Yahoo! account:  \r\n \r\nThis user doesn\'t have                          a yahoo.com account (jaywise9@yahoo.com). \r\n \r\nDoes this account exist, and if not, can I have a new email to put you on the listserv? \r\n \r\nThanks, \r\nScott Heggen'),(40,139,39,0,'Jason Black','2011-09-10 14:57:56','RE:Listserv error','Not sure, because this is my email.  You can also add me using jblack@cis.famu.edu'),(41,77,39,0,'Scott Heggen','2011-09-11 03:29:53','RE:Listserv error','Thanks Jason.  If the error persists, I\'ll swap it out for the other address.  \n\n-Scott'),(42,45,35,0,'Heather Lipford','2011-09-12 19:22:37','RE:Community Resources','That\'s a great idea Veronica. We did not collect the celebration posters this year as far as I know, and none have been posted on this site yet. But let me ask Karen, and perhaps she can email the schools and encourage them to have their students upload their posters here.\n\nIn the meantime, you could post a message to the outreach affinity group, and ask if anyone had a poster to upload it to the affinity group or send it to you.'),(43,294,43,0,'Amul Adagale','2011-09-13 15:38:37','oh come on.. u cannot send a msg without a subject','just learning'),(44,77,43,0,'Scott Heggen','2011-09-13 16:36:53','RE:oh come on.. u cannot send a msg without a subject','Your the technical support for this.... fix it!\n'),(45,42,45,1,'Administrator','2011-09-15 01:50:39',';)','hehe'),(46,302,46,0,'Kim RoSser','2011-09-21 13:24:40','geek fest','Is it at Levine campus again? \r\nI\'m not sure who\'s in charge of the website, but it only shows last years info.'),(47,102,47,0,'Bonita O\'Banion','2011-09-24 23:07:42','Committees','I would like to be a part of the community service committee.'),(48,139,47,0,'Jason Black','2011-09-24 23:09:00','RE:Committees','Thanks'),(49,102,47,0,'Bonita O\'Banion','2011-09-25 21:07:03','RE:Committees','And I would also be willing to travel to Niceville on the 28th.'),(50,82,50,0,'Nikunja Swain','2011-09-26 18:03:45','Test','This is a test.'),(51,153,51,0,'Brian Richards','2011-10-02 18:42:41','STARS Celebration Speech','Dear Dr. Barnes,\r\n\r\nI wrote this spur of the moment before everyone else woke up on the last day of the celebration, as I couldn\'t sleep due to the excitement of returning home coupled with not wanting to leave the Celebration.  I hope you enjoy it.\r\n\r\n\"Hello everyone.  If I could steal your attention away from this wonderful continental breakfast, or as I like to call it, \"the extra two hours of sleep before the keynote speaker.\"  I just wanted to take a few moments to reflect on my first, and certainly not my last trip to the STARS Alliance Celebration.  For those of you who haven\'t met me through the snag-em game, at a session, or in the hot tub at the pool after a long day of meetings, my name is Brian Richards and I am an undergraduate Computer Science major at the University of New Orleans.  This entire conference has been a completely life changing experience for me and I hope it has affected all of you as well.  When I first arrived here at the Hilton, I was very nervous, anxious and even terrified because I did not really know what I was doing or even what I expected to get from what turned out to be the most exciting three days of my Computer Science career.  Although my faculty adviser was unable to attend, I met Marguerite Doman on the first day and she reassured me that everything would be fine and that this was a really laid-back experience.  This really helped with the negative emotions and I would like to extend my personal gratitude to her for making it easier.  After that everything went completely smooth.  I signed up for Evie Powell\'s research project; the snag-em game.  For those of you who did not get a chance to play this year, whether it was because you played before or you just did not know about it, I would highly recommend it for next year.  It is a very fun way to extend you social network and meet new people.  I would like to congratulate Kai Dumont on having the most points, but just know I\'ll be coming after that title next year.  When I first got here I was unsure about going to Graduate school after obtaining my bachelor\'s degree.  Now I can confidently say after listening to the keynote and workshop speakers, that it is now an important career goal for me to accomplish.  I will also take as much of the wonderful information I got from the keynotes and meetings and use it to better the Computer Science department at UNO.  I met alot of very interesting people here and I cannot wait to see all of you at next year\'s Celebration, along with some new faces as well.  Thank you.\"\r\n\r\nSorry it took me a while to get back to you on this, as my Computer Science classes have been very demanding this semester.  Also, I was wondering if I could get some advise from you on internships, as I have a few questions about it.  Thanks for providing so much entertainment at the Night at the Museum and I hope you have a wonderful semester.\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\n\r\nBrian Richards'),(52,122,51,0,'Tiffany Barnes','2011-10-03 16:14:31','RE:STARS Celebration Speech','Thank you Brian! Is it okay with you if I send this around to STARS faculty and share with Evie?\n\nNo problem about taking some time to get it to me! :)\n\nSure I am happy to answer questions about internships though I have to admit that I don\'t have a lot of direct connections to them. I will do better connecting you to undergraduate research opportunities. You can schedule a 30-minute call with me on tungle.me/tiffanybarnes\n\nTiffany Barnes\n'),(53,153,51,0,'Brian Richards','2011-10-03 16:28:30','RE:STARS Celebration Speech','It is okay to share this with whoever you would like.  I have scheduled a time to speak with you and look forward to speaking with you.  \n\nThanks again,\n\nBrian Richards'),(54,122,51,0,'Tiffany Barnes','2011-10-07 14:12:08','RE:STARS Celebration Speech','Thanks Brian. What\'s your email address? So we can email directly?\n\nTiffany Barnes'),(55,82,55,0,'Nikunja Swain','2011-10-10 16:21:22','Meeting Reminder','When: October 12, 2011 (wednesday) \r\nWhere: NH 317 \r\nWhat time: 5:30 PM \r\nAttendance is Required \r\n \r\nDr. Swain'),(56,318,56,0,'Cheryl Seals','2011-10-10 21:38:09','Hi Carla','Hi Carla, \r\nDr. Seals here the AU leader, just checking to see if you are in the Auburn area.  If so email me at sealscd@auburn.edu so that we can get you signed up officially in case we have stipends available.  Have a great day, Dr. Seals'),(57,326,56,0,'Carla Pelazzi','2011-10-10 23:19:38','RE:Hi Carla','Hi Dr. Seals!\nThis is \"Rose-Gaelle\". I never use my real name on social networking sites for privacy reasons.\nI hope that you had a wonderful week-end! :)\n--\nR-G'),(58,231,58,0,'Lila Mandela','2011-10-12 01:01:24','Hack-a-thon','Goood day STARS professional development committee....aka sharielle. I am lila mandela, your committee chair for the 2011-2012 academic year. I\'ll be spreading out information concerning the different events we\'ll be organizing and how we can all work together to execute our projects successfully. I recently spoke with antony jepson, the famu microsoft representative. He\'ll be hosting a hack-a-thon event on november 3 at the cis building (date subject to change). It will last from 10:00 am to 2:00 pm. Antony needs our assistance in reserving rooms, installing software and other items. since the group is so tiny, we\'ll all be doing a lot of work. I hope for success in the end. If you have any questions, please e-mail me your concerns with the title &quot; hack-a-thon&quot; so i\'ll know to respond swiftly. E-Mail me at lmandela91@gmail.com. Thanks for joining the committee! ~lila~'),(59,281,59,0,'angel bobo','2011-10-12 16:32:01','Outreach/Education','Hey ladies we are going to meet twice a month to talk about outreach opportunities, and ideas that we have. I would like for you guys to give me your days that you are available. You can contact me at (209) 496-5292.'),(60,281,60,0,'angel bobo','2011-10-13 00:37:14','Outreach/Education','Hey ladies this is Angel Bobo, Chair of Outreach/Educational \r\nCommittee. Right now I would like to meet at least once \r\na month to discuss ideas for what we should do, in our  \r\ncommittee. Please give me days and times of availability, \r\nso that I can try to get everyone to meet at times that  \r\nwork for the majority if us. My phone number is (209)496-5292. \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\nThank you, \r\n \r\n \r\nAngel Bobo'),(61,281,61,0,'angel bobo','2011-10-13 00:41:24','Education/Outreach','Hey ladies this is Angel Bobo, Chair of Outreach/Educational \r\nCommittee. Right now I would like to meet at least once \r\na month to discuss ideas for what we should do, in our  \r\ncommittee. Please give me days and times of availability, \r\nso that I can try to get every