 are interested in submitting something for me to look at. Let me know what you think!'),(67,244,67,0,'Luis Figueroa','2011-10-14 16:34:51','Stars Interviews.','The C.S. professor you are going to meet is Mr.R.Choudhari located in Nance R.m. 329. His office hours are from 10-11 and 12-12:30 Wednesday. \r\nThe M. professor you are going to meet is Mr.K.Adzievski located in Nance 325. His office hours are from 1:50-2:30 Wednesday.   \r\n \r\nIf they are not available at the time specified then see their office hours schedule located on their doors.'),(68,244,68,0,'Luis Figueroa','2011-10-14 16:38:44','Interviews.','The C.S. professor you are going to meet is Dr.Y.Kim located in Moss R.m. 104-C. His office hours are from 3-4p.m.Wednesday. \r\nThe M. professor you are going to meet is Mr.R.Ali located in Nance 305. His office hours are from 5-6p.m. Wednesday.   \r\n \r\nIf they are not available at the time specified then see their office hours schedule located on their doors.'),(69,244,69,0,'Luis Figueroa','2011-10-14 16:43:57','Interview.','The C.S. professor you are going to meet is Dr.Z.Zografski located in Nance R.m. 210. His office hours are from 11-12 Wednesday. \r\nThe M. professor you are going to meet is Ms.V.W.Green located in Nance 305. His office hours are from 12-1:00 Wednesday.   \r\n \r\nIf they are not available at the time specified then see their office hours schedule located on their doors.'),(70,163,61,0,'Jessica Herd','2011-10-16 22:31:28','RE:Education/Outreach','M, W, F \n'),(71,332,66,0,'Jessica Michel','2011-10-17 06:09:54','RE:Logo and Design','Sorry I volunteered with Susan G Komen all weekend and am just now able to get to my computer. Yes I work with graphic design. What are you looking for in the new design? Off hand I know the star needs to be turned into a vector (allows the logo to be really big or small and still look very sharp). I do have a few projects from school and a rough draft of a logo I did for a club in the school we are waiting for approval for.'),(72,341,72,0,'Anisah Kabli','2011-10-30 17:17:28','STARS Video','Hii,  \r\n \r\nSorry to bother, but I was wondering if you could point me in some direction for the video. I\'m in charge of doing it and I really don\'t know what its supposed to be (besides the time limit) \r\n \r\nI was wondering what you were doing for it, i.e recorded video or flash? \r\n \r\nThanks so much, \r\n \r\nAnisah'),(73,118,72,0,'Jenny LeMieux','2011-10-30 22:55:12','RE:STARS Video','I am happy to help you as best I can, but I am not working on the YouTube video myself.  I am an adjunct Faculty for SSC and I am the \"EA\".  I am happy to put you in touch with the students who will be working on this at SSC, but I know they won\'t really have a chance to get started until after an event on 11-11-11.  In the meantime, I found the link to FSU\'s YouTube video so you could see an example.  Here it is - http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RgLMFQFgRE0'),(74,341,72,0,'Anisah Kabli','2011-10-31 00:21:31','RE:STARS Video','Oh thanks so much!\n\nThe link was very helpful to get some idea of what to do. \n\nI was wondering if there was any rubric about what I\'d have to include or the format?\n\nThanks again :)\n\nAnisah'),(75,293,75,0,'Gloria Szilasi','2011-10-31 01:23:25','Hey',' hey i wanted to test out if this works here! :) '),(76,118,72,0,'Jenny LeMieux','2011-11-03 01:11:23','RE:STARS Video','Not that I am aware of - it sounds like they want to give us a lot of creative freedom!  Good luck!'),(77,231,58,0,'Lila Mandela','2011-11-08 10:07:41','RE:Hack-a-thon','hola\n\nUPDATES!\n\n I think I told some  of you guys about the proposed MSFT hack-a-thon that we were planning to host this semester. It\'s going to be moved to the spring and so right now we just need to get the word out so that people can be preparing over the winter break. Since we\'re supposed to be using the STARS website, you\'ll also be receiving this message there as well. I\'m still working with Antony Jepson on the event. He\'s going to speak at the AAWCS meeting not only about the event, but the internships available at MSFT (I\'ll confirm it with Dr. Black). We as a group haven\'t really been informing each other about our ideas for the committee. Hopefully this will get better. Please let me know of any ideas or questions. Let\'s do our best!\n\n~Lila Mandela~'),(78,163,78,0,'Jessica Herd','2011-11-08 15:32:23','BlackBusinesses in Silicon Valley','I know you are over Social Events so I wanted to see if you would be interested in hosting a movie night Sunday Nov 13th 8pm. CNN is running a TV viewing on Black Business Owners who started their own business in Silicon Valley. Silicon Valley is known for creating technological companies. If we can find a place that has a large flat screen and seats, we as a group could watch the viewing since its CIS related. What do you think?'),(79,224,78,0,'Melanie Mitchell','2011-11-08 16:30:18','RE:BlackBusinesses in Silicon Valley','that sounds great. i was thinking of doing something similar to this but i just needed an event for the social. the only thing is that i\'m going to be out of town this weekend and i don\'t know what time i will be back on sunday'),(80,165,58,0,'Sharielle Johnson','2011-11-08 18:30:08','RE:Hack-a-thon','sounds good!'),(81,122,81,0,'Tiffany Barnes','2011-11-22 17:29:59','Great to see you at GHC too!',':) Fun dancing!'),(82,458,82,0,'anita','2011-11-28 12:45:02','anita1soumah@yahoo.com','Hi Dear, \r\n \r\nHow are you doing? With hope you are doing great!  My name is Ms anita a young good looking girl searching for true love/friendship, I came across your profile today when i was browsing through web site and i became interested in Dear contact me by my email ID (anita1soumah@yahoo.com) so i can give you my pictures to you. \r\nand i will like to know more about you if you don\'t mind to mail me back so that i can give you my pictures and tell you more about myself. \r\n(anita1soumah@yahoo.com) \r\n \r\n