012-10-29 16:18:28','Join SSC group!','Join SSC group!'),(112,352,112,0,'Marcus Wells','2012-11-05 17:40:27','Hello Dr.B','Hello'),(113,127,112,0,'Chutima Boonthum-Denecke','2012-11-05 17:45:37','RE:Hello Dr.B','Hi, Don\'t forget to register for CIA 695. :-)'),(114,912,114,0,'Dan Lucey','2012-11-07 20:12:25','serious games for Haitian children.','Ms. Doran. Have you been to Haiti? If so what is it like there? How does your program work? I would like to learn more about the work you are doing for Haitian kids.'),(115,912,115,0,'Dan Lucey','2012-11-09 23:53:25','STARS registration','Professor Gentry-Kolen, \r\nI have registered for the NWFSC STARS group.'),(116,125,115,0,'Heidi  Gentry-Kolen','2012-11-10 22:05:26','RE:STARS registration','SUPER!  Thanks, Dan.\nHeidi'),(117,421,114,0,'Katelyn Doran','2012-11-12 23:46:28','RE:serious games for Haitian children.','Hi Dan,\n\nSTARS Haiti is a really cool opportunity to share our skills with students, mentors, and educators in rural northern Haiti.  Haiti is an incredibly unique country with a complex history - I\'m far from qualified to speak to all of the details of Haitian history and culture, but th book Haiti After the Earthquake by Paul Farmer is fantastic if you\'d like to learn more about the country.  STARS Haiti is a partnership with three affiliated schools in Haitit that were recipients of One Laptop Per Child XO computers.  Our role has been helping the schools to best leverage the XO\'s by teaching them what the full potential of the laptops really is, helping to support infrastructure (such as setting up a One Laptop Per Child School Server), and providing mentorship and resources.  If you have other specific questions, please let me know - I\'m happy to answer them!'),(118,771,118,0,'T. Ray Campbell','2012-11-13 17:41:35','2012 Narrative Report','Hi Dr. Rorrer, \r\nI have been trying to submit the Narrative for Livingstone College STARS initiative before 11/15, but cannot find any link on the web site to do so. Appreciate if you could point me to the link to submit. \r\n \r\nThanks, \r\n \r\nT. Ray Campbell \r\nrcampbell@livingstone.edu'),(120,912,114,0,'Dan Lucey','2012-11-14 20:19:48','RE:serious games for Haitian children.','cool, I\'ll definitely check out the book. Thanks.'),(121,862,121,0,'Mark Boutwell','2012-11-16 21:11:05','admin','Could you make me an admin for the Northwest Florida State College group? \r\n'),(122,42,121,0,'Administrator','2012-11-18 20:58:04','RE:admin','Done. You should be able to post announcements now.'),(123,862,121,0,'Mark Boutwell','2012-11-19 02:17:49','RE:admin','Thank you'),(124,862,124,0,'Mark Boutwell','2012-12-08 17:38:08','ethernet','Hey, could you explain what you had in mind with the ethernet cable again? seperating the wires? what kind of data will be sent? Could you give me an example of the data packets being sent? \r\nI\'m putting together a schematic and this information will be much appreciated.'),(125,395,125,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-08 20:13:53','Speaker for UNCC event','Hi Shaun, \r\n \r\nI hope you are doing well!  We are underway with our plans for the Julia Robinson Math and Computing Festival, an event which invites middle school girls on campus to investigate diverse areas of mathematics and computing they would not ordinarily encounter in the classroom. The day includes several math and computing activity stations where girls can learn about different aspects of each discipline and ends with a presentation by an invited speaker. (http://education.uncc.edu/oeo/events/julia-robinson-mathematics-and-computing-festival) \r\n \r\nIn an effort to increase the presence of computing at this event, we are seeking an interactive and fun female presenter that can keep this demographic of girls engaged and build excitement about computing. Last year, we had a little over 200 girls in attendance, and expect about the same next year. The date of our next festival is tentatively set for Saturday, March 30, 2013.  If you know of any dynamic women that you think would be interested, could you please forward me their contact information?  Or, feel free to have them contact me at aubrae.collins@uncc.edu. \r\n \r\nThanks so much! \r\nAubrae'),(126,395,126,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-08 20:18:40','Contact info for Evie Powell','Hi Veronica! \r\n \r\nWe\'re trying to secure a speaker for the Julia Robinson Math and Computing Festival for this year and Evie came to mind.  I know she is in Seattle now (I think)but I would still like to invite her.  Do you have an email address for her?  Or, would you mind asking her to email me at aubrae.collins@uncc.edu? \r\n \r\nThanks! \r\nAubrae'),(127,273,126,0,'Veronica Catete','2013-01-08 20:23:52','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','Evie\'s new email: epowell@microsoft.com.\n\nIf she is unavailable, Katie Doran  just got a job with Mircosoft XBOX, and she did an 8 month internship out there.\n\n'),(128,395,126,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-08 21:44:49','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','Oh, great.  Do you also have an email address for Katie?  Is she local?\n\nThanks!\nAubrae'),(129,273,126,0,'Veronica Catete','2013-01-08 21:49:07','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','doran.katelyn@gmail.com '),(130,273,126,0,'Veronica Catete','2013-01-08 21:50:00','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','She is local currently, I\'m not sure when she goes back to seattle though.  '),(131,395,126,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-08 21:55:33','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','Ok, thanks.  You\'ve been a great help!'),(132,395,126,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-08 21:57:59','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','Actually, one last question.  Do you have an email address for Shaun Pickford?  Thanks!'),(133,273,126,0,'Veronica Catete','2013-01-08 22:00:50','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','shaun.pickford@gmail.com'),(134,395,126,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-08 22:01:20','RE:Contact info for Evie Powell','Thank you!'),(135,848,135,0,'Annette Clifford','2013-01-09 21:29:25','STARS Group','Hi Laura, \r\n \r\nAny luck on finding a date yet? \r\n \r\nAC'),(136,949,136,0,'Angela Gonzales','2013-01-10 22:10:30','Hey there!','Just thought that I should say hi and to let you know that I joined the group. =^_^='),(137,835,137,0,'Michael Nguyen','2013-01-12 04:27:07','REPLY: STARS stipend','I\'m sorry but I am unfamiliar with who you are and I have already submitted a auto-deposit form for my stipend. I don\'t see how my home address is necessary for a electronic deposit. I don\'t mean any offence. It\'s not that I don\'t trust you; it\'s because I cannot trust everyone. '),(138,395,137,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-14 12:48:23','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','Hi Michael,\n\nI understand.  I am the Program Coordinator for the STARS program at UNC Charlotte.  When there are multiple people with the same name in our Banner system, we use home address to verify we have the ID number for the correct person.  You can either call me at 704-687-8954 or give your information to your Academic Liaison (Lydia Fritz is who I normally communicate with) and have her contact me with the information.\n\nThank you,\nAubrae'),(139,77,139,0,'Scott Heggen','2013-01-14 15:15:35','Event Administrators','Hi Heather, \r\n \r\nDoes the community have the ability to let me add people as event administrators? I\'d like to make Karen and the Team Leaders admins to events so they can add more detailed information without having to go through me each time.  \r\n \r\nThanks, \r\nScott'),(140,77,140,0,'Scott Heggen','2013-01-14 15:29:56','Science Fair Judging','Hi James, \r\n \r\nThanks for registering to judge at the Science Fair. It\'s very short notice, but you need to contact Ms. Simpson (dhartgen@vnet.net) and let her know you plan to attend, and get any additional information from her, and also make sure she still needs another judge. Please CC myself (sheggen@uncc.edu) on that email so I know it\'s been done. \r\n \r\nLet me know what else you need to make the event a success. \r\n \r\nRegards, \r\nScott'),(141,835,141,0,'Michael Nguyen','2013-01-15 19:18:01','STARS stipend information','I am providing my home address for authentication purposes in order to receive the stipend. Thank you. \r\nHome address: 13748 Laurianne Ter Gainesville, VA 20155 \r\n \r\nFWD: STARS stipend \r\n&quot;Hi Michael, \r\n \r\nI understand. I am the Program Coordinator for the STARS program at UNC Charlotte. When there are multiple people with the same name in our Banner system, we use home address to verify we have the ID number for the correct person. You can either call me at 704-687-8954 or give your information to your Academic Liaison (Lydia Fritz is who I normally communicate with) and have her contact me with the information. \r\n \r\nThank you, \r\nAubrae \r\n&quot;'),(142,835,137,0,'Michael Nguyen','2013-01-16 04:40:03','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','I sent a private message to Lydia Fritz that included our conversation and my home address. I will also include my home address in this converstation for your own reference. Thank you for you reply and allowing me to be a part of the program.\nHome address:\n13748 Laurianne Ter\nGainesville, VA 20155'),(143,395,137,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-16 14:47:50','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','Great, thanks!'),(144,395,137,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-16 19:23:05','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','Hi Michael,\n\nThere is no Michael Nguyen in our system with your home address, so it looks like your form was not processed. Did you fax or mail in your form? I also mistakenly thought you attended UNCG and that\'s why I mentioned Lydia Fritz.  I realize now that you attend George Mason and your Academic Liaison is Kammy Sanghera.  I will send her an email asking you to submit another form.  If you can submit this form by the end of this week, we can process your fall stipend now instead of later this semester with your spring stipend.\n\nThanks,\nAubrae'),(145,77,145,0,'Scott Heggen','2013-01-16 20:20:17','Blacks at Microsoft (BAM) event','Hi Veronica,\r\n\r\nHow are things?\r\n\r\nBAM will be hosting hosts its annual BAM Minority Student Day (BMSD) on Friday, February 15th at the Microsoft Charlotte Campus.  Through word-of-mouth I was told you ran the booth last year, and they were so impressed and happy with the activity that you did, they wanted UNCC to bring it back.  Do you still have the content you delivered, and any instructions I can give to our students on how to facilitate the booth?\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\nScott'),(146,835,137,0,'Michael Nguyen','2013-01-17 02:32:12','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','Hello Aubrae,\n\nYou are correct that my university is George Mason and my Academic Liaison is Kammy. I gave all my forms and a voided check to Kammy during the middle of the semester. She reviewed them and ensured they were filled out correctly. I entrusted her to process them. I have already sent her an email last week and phoned her today. No reply. The last piece of information I received from her was that the stipend would be \"processed by January\". I checked my online banking and have no received it yet. If you are able to get in contact with her please let me know what the situation is. I contacted another member in the GMU STARS program and she has not received her stipend either.\n\nThank you.\nMichael'),(147,395,137,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-17 12:47:06','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','Michael,\n\nI\'ll follow up with Kammy.  Who is the other student that said she has not received her stipend?'),(148,273,145,0,'Veronica Catete','2013-01-17 22:30:29','RE:Blacks at Microsoft (BAM) event','Hey Scott, \n\n I\'ve been running a GameMaker workshop with Microsoft Charlotte for several years now, unfortunately I\'ll be across the country at another Microsoft event this day.  Carla has run the GameMaker tutorial several times with me. \n\nI\'ve put together some stuff for the maze game tutorial.  It includes project resources, a step by step PDF, as well as a finished version of the game.  Most of my old SPARCS team is familiar with it.  \n\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/sh/4gsk3i5nc48umne/pFEy-qa3qX/Game Maker Resources\n\nI would recommend that anyone who is going to go to skim through the tutorial pdf, and try to build the game themselves. It should only take about 10 minutes to become familiar with game maker.  The workshop with the students should take 30-45 minutes, Microsoft should send you more details as the time nears.  Usually I get 3-4 groups of about 25 students who come to do the workshop. One of the things we try to do is give the girls challenges after the tutorial part is over, such as adding bombs, enemies, or some other interactive piece (locked doors etc).\n\nOh yeah, and as far as I know this won\'t be a \"booth\" as one would think, it\'s a separate classroom where the groups will circulate through throughout the day. There is a projector, and computers for all of the students. Internet access if needed, will have to be asked for. In the past we had the GameMaker installer on a flash drive, and installed it on the computers that way.  There is also a shared folder that can be installed to, that the other machines should have access to. \n\nAs far as installation goes, grab GameMaker lite from http://yoyogames.com/gamemaker/download.  The resources folder should be copied and placed on the machines.  We found it easiest if it was on the desktop.  Not all of these students are familiar with things like double clicking and computer navigation.\n\nI think that\'s most of my insider\'s scoop.  Other than what I\'ve mentioned just tell them to have fun and feel free to grab free drinks from the fridge in the hallway, I like making the hot cocoa. Let me know if you come up with anymore questions, or need last minute help on things. I\'ll do my best to help.\n\n~Veronica\n'),(149,835,137,0,'Michael Nguyen','2013-01-18 02:21:29','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','I got into contact with Kammy. Kammy instructed Summaya Mazhar and I to filled out the Vendor Information form again and faxed it to the number (704) 687-6514, before Saturday. I have done so and sent the form. Please let me know if there is any other issue. Thank you.'),(150,395,137,0,'Aubrae Collins','2013-01-18 13:54:36','RE:REPLY: STARS stipend','Thanks for the update, Michael.  I\'ll follow up when everything is received and set up.'),(151,77,145,0,'Scott Heggen','2013-01-18 15:39:33','RE:Blacks at Microsoft (BAM) event','Hey Veronica,\n\nI love working with you.  You always give more that I ever expect!\n\nI will pass this along to the students attending this year.  Have fun in Redmond, and say Hi to Katie and crew for me (I\'m boldly assuming that\'s where you\'ll be).\n\nRegards,\nScott'),(152,620,152,0,'Robinson Udechukwu','2013-01-19 20:02:56','Ref: Stipends and next meeting','Your note went out to the entire STARS Corps but if that was not what you intended, you might want to send a correction or you will get entries from STARS members outside of your school in your Doodle.'),(153,741,153,0,'alexis ellis','2013-01-21 18:09:10','stipend file','i received an email from you regarding the stipend but i have not received the file that needs to be filled out. '),(154,69,154,0,'Karen Bean','2013-01-22 18:33:25','your post regarding stipend application','Jonathan, who did you intend to see your message about the stipend application? I am getting many questions as the STARS office did not send this.  Was this just for your group?  Can you please clarify for all recipients in the Online community?  Thanks, \r\nKaren Bean'),(155,876,154,0,'Jonathan Howard','2013-01-23 23:10:50','RE:your post regarding stipend application','I am so embarrassed, it was just for my school. I\'ve moved the post.'),(156,876,153,0,'Jonathan Howard','2013-01-23 23:11:18','RE:stipend file','I am so embarrassed, it was just for my school. I\'ve moved the post.'),(157,876,152,0,'Jonathan Howard','2013-01-23 23:11:42','RE:Ref: Stipends and next meeting','I am so embarrassed, it was just for my school. I\'v